name: 03-Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
content:
Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

Data Profiling:

  • Count of towers and neighbor relationships.
  • Distribution of dropped calls vs. successful calls across towers.

Descriptive Analysis:

  • Geographic Distribution: Mapping towers and their nearest neighbors.
  • Connectivity Patterns: High vs. low connectivity success rates.
  • Dropped Call Analysis: Identifying towers with frequent failures.
  • Load Analysis: Average network load per tower and its impact on call quality.

Visualizations:

  • Heatmap of neighbor connectivity strengths.
  • Scatter plot of distance vs. call success rate.
  • Bar charts of top 10 towers with highest dropped calls.
